WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.200
Oxford Bookworms, Stage 1.

00:04.600 --> 00:10.400
Christmas in Prague, by Joyce Hanham, read by Jill Schilling.

00:11.200 --> 00:17.000
Published and copyright, Oxford University Press 2005.

00:30.000 --> 00:45.000
Chapter 1. Christmas 1957.

00:46.000 --> 00:53.000
It is night, and the fields near the village are white with snow.

00:54.000 --> 01:00.000
The village is quiet, but not everybody is sleeping.

01:01.000 --> 01:05.000
Eyes are watching the roads and the fields near the village

01:06.000 --> 01:13.000
because this is Czechoslovakia, and the year is 1957.

01:14.000 --> 01:23.000
Across the fields, only half a kilometre away is the Austrian border,

01:24.000 --> 01:30.000
but the people of Czechoslovakia are not free to go to Austria.

01:31.000 --> 01:37.000
The border guards watch day and night, and they carry guns.

01:38.000 --> 01:44.000
In a house in the village, a man and a woman are talking.

01:45.000 --> 01:51.000
The woman holds a six-month-old baby boy in her arms.

01:52.000 --> 01:57.000
She is excited, but she is afraid too.

01:58.000 --> 02:01.000
Tell me again, she says.

02:02.000 --> 02:06.000
Did he get to Austria all right last night?

02:07.000 --> 02:10.000
Yes, he did, the man says.

02:11.000 --> 02:15.000
Nobody saw him, nobody heard him.

02:16.000 --> 02:21.000
But last night was easy, because the sky was dark.

02:22.000 --> 02:25.000
Tonight, it's more difficult.

02:25.000 --> 02:28.000
Look at that moon.

02:29.000 --> 02:33.000
But it's Christmas night, the woman says,

02:34.000 --> 02:38.000
and the guards are drinking in the guardhouse, yes?

02:39.000 --> 02:42.000
That's true, says the man.

02:43.000 --> 02:48.000
But sometimes they come out and drive up and down the road for a time.

02:49.000 --> 02:54.000
So you must be careful, and you must run fast.

02:55.000 --> 02:59.000
Very fast. He looks at his watch.

03:00.000 --> 03:03.000
It's time to go.

03:04.000 --> 03:08.000
The woman puts on a white coat and a white hat.

03:09.000 --> 03:12.000
The baby wears a white coat too,

03:13.000 --> 03:17.000
and the woman carries him on her back.

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
Good, the man says.

03:21.000 --> 03:24.000
White is best when there's snow.

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
Nobody can see you.

03:27.000 --> 03:31.000
Now, are you ready? Let's go.

03:32.000 --> 03:37.000
They leave the house and walk quickly out of the village.

03:38.000 --> 03:45.000
After a time, they stop, and the man says very quietly,

03:46.000 --> 03:49.000
OK. Do you see those trees?

03:51.000 --> 03:54.000
Turn right there and go 50 meters.

03:56.000 --> 03:59.000
When you come to the road, go across it quickly,

04:00.000 --> 04:03.000
and run down the hill through the trees.

04:04.000 --> 04:06.000
Then you come to the river.

04:07.000 --> 04:10.000
Turn left and go 500 meters.

04:11.000 --> 04:16.000
The trees finish there, and you can walk through the river easily.

04:17.000 --> 04:21.000
Across two more fields, and you're in Austria.

04:22.000 --> 04:25.000
Our friends are waiting for you in the second field.

04:26.000 --> 04:27.000
Go now.

04:28.000 --> 04:29.000
Goodbye.

04:30.000 --> 04:31.000
And good luck.

04:32.000 --> 04:34.000
The woman begins to run.

04:35.000 --> 04:37.000
The baby on her back is sleeping.

04:38.000 --> 04:43.000
But now, he opens his eyes and begins to cry.

04:44.000 --> 04:48.000
The woman is afraid and runs more slowly.

04:49.000 --> 04:52.000
But the baby's crying is loud in the night.

04:53.000 --> 04:57.000
At the trees, the woman turns right,

04:58.000 --> 05:00.000
and soon she is at the road.

05:02.000 --> 05:06.000
She does not see the black car under the trees.

05:07.000 --> 05:10.000
But the men in the car see her.

05:11.000 --> 05:16.000
Suddenly, there is a noise in the night, the noise of guns.

05:18.000 --> 05:20.000
Then it is quiet again.

05:21.000 --> 05:25.000
The woman's body lies in the snow on the road.

05:26.000 --> 05:31.000
Now, the only sound is the crying of the baby.

05:37.000 --> 05:40.000
The woman's body lies in the snow on the road.

05:46.000 --> 05:47.000
Chapter 2

05:48.000 --> 05:51.000
England 1995

05:54.000 --> 05:58.000
Hey! Jan, look at this!

05:59.000 --> 06:00.000
Carol said.

06:01.000 --> 06:03.000
She had a letter in her hand

06:04.000 --> 06:08.000
and took it across to her husband at the breakfast table.

06:09.000 --> 06:12.000
It's from the Oxford Orchestra, she said.

06:13.000 --> 06:17.000
They're giving concerts in the Czech Republic this Christmas.

06:18.000 --> 06:21.000
They're doing three concerts in Prague

06:22.000 --> 06:26.000
and they're asking me to go because they need a harpist.

06:27.000 --> 06:30.000
Shall we go to Prague for Christmas?

06:31.000 --> 06:35.000
I can play with the orchestra and you can come with us.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.000
When are the concerts?

06:39.000 --> 06:40.000
Asked Jan.

06:41.000 --> 06:45.000
I always have a lot of work in the weeks before Christmas.

06:46.000 --> 06:49.000
I must finish writing my new book then.

06:51.000 --> 06:54.000
Jan taught Czech at Oxford University

06:55.000 --> 06:57.000
and wrote books about languages.

06:58.000 --> 07:01.000
He was born in Czechoslovakia

07:02.000 --> 07:06.000
but came to England with his father when he was very young.

07:08.000 --> 07:12.000
He met Carol when she was one of his students at university.

07:14.000 --> 07:18.000
The first concert is on December the 20th.

07:19.000 --> 07:20.000
Carol answered.

07:21.000 --> 07:22.000
Are you free then?

07:23.000 --> 07:24.000
No.

07:25.000 --> 07:26.000
I'm sorry Carol.

07:27.000 --> 07:28.000
Jan said.

07:29.000 --> 07:32.000
But I can't come before December the 24th.

07:34.000 --> 07:36.000
Well, it doesn't matter.

07:37.000 --> 07:40.000
You can come for the second concert.

07:41.000 --> 07:43.000
It's on December the 25th.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.000
But what about my father?

07:47.000 --> 07:48.000
Said Jan.

07:49.000 --> 07:52.000
We can't go away and leave him at Christmas time.

07:53.000 --> 07:56.000
He loves a family Christmas with us.

07:57.000 --> 07:58.000
You know that.

08:01.000 --> 08:04.000
Jose Flách was 68 years old

08:05.000 --> 08:07.000
and his eyes were bad.

08:09.000 --> 08:11.000
He couldn't see very well.

08:12.000 --> 08:14.000
So he lived with Carol and Jan.

08:15.000 --> 08:17.000
Josef can come with us.

08:18.000 --> 08:19.000
Carol said.

08:20.000 --> 08:23.000
He often talks about Prague at Christmas.

08:24.000 --> 08:28.000
He says it's the most beautiful time of the year there

08:29.000 --> 08:32.000
because of all the snow on the old buildings.

08:34.000 --> 08:35.000
I know.

08:36.000 --> 08:37.000
Said Jan.

08:38.000 --> 08:40.000
But he only talks about Prague.

08:41.000 --> 08:43.000
He never wants to go there.

08:44.000 --> 08:47.000
Every time we ask him to come with us,

08:48.000 --> 08:49.000
he says no.

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
I don't know why,

08:53.000 --> 08:55.000
but I think it's because of my mother.

08:56.000 --> 08:58.000
When he thinks about Prague,

08:59.000 --> 09:00.000
he remembers her.

09:02.000 --> 09:03.000
You know,

09:04.000 --> 09:07.000
sometimes he cries when he looks at his photo of her.

09:07.000 --> 09:09.000
After all these years.

09:14.000 --> 09:21.000
Just then, the door opened and Jan's father came slowly into the room.

09:22.000 --> 09:23.000
Good morning.

09:24.000 --> 09:27.000
He said and sat down at the table.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
Is there any coffee?

09:31.000 --> 09:32.000
It's cold now.

09:33.000 --> 09:34.000
Said Carol.

09:34.000 --> 09:36.000
Shall I make you some more?

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
Thank you, my dear.

09:40.000 --> 09:41.000
He answered.

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
You're very good to me.

09:45.000 --> 09:48.000
Carol went out for some coffee.

09:49.000 --> 09:52.000
Jan looked at his father carefully.

09:54.000 --> 09:56.000
I must ask him now.

09:57.000 --> 09:58.000
He thought.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.000
While Carol is out of the room,

10:02.000 --> 10:04.000
you're very quiet, Jan.

10:05.000 --> 10:07.000
Said the old man.

10:08.000 --> 10:09.000
Is something wrong?

10:10.000 --> 10:11.000
No, no.

10:12.000 --> 10:14.000
Said Jan quickly.

10:15.000 --> 10:16.000
Nothing's wrong.

10:17.000 --> 10:18.000
It's just,

10:19.000 --> 10:21.000
I want to ask you a question,

10:22.000 --> 10:23.000
but

10:25.000 --> 10:26.000
it's difficult.

10:26.000 --> 10:27.000
Jan stopped.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.000
His father smiled.

10:37.000 --> 10:38.000
Difficult?

10:39.000 --> 10:41.000
Why is it difficult?

10:42.000 --> 10:45.000
Are you afraid of an old man?

10:46.000 --> 10:48.000
Of course not.

10:49.000 --> 10:50.000
Said Jan.

10:51.000 --> 10:54.000
But I am afraid of your answer.

10:55.000 --> 10:59.000
You see, Carol wants to go very much.

11:00.000 --> 11:03.000
She loves playing her harp,

11:04.000 --> 11:06.000
but it's Christmas time and

11:07.000 --> 11:08.000
stop,

11:09.000 --> 11:10.000
said Joseph.

11:11.000 --> 11:12.000
What are you talking about?

11:13.000 --> 11:16.000
Where does Carol want to go at Christmas?

11:18.000 --> 11:19.000
To Prague,

11:20.000 --> 11:21.000
said Jan.

11:22.000 --> 11:24.000
And I would like to go with her.

11:25.000 --> 11:27.000
We want you to come too.

11:29.000 --> 11:30.000
Ah.

11:31.000 --> 11:32.000
Said the old man.

11:33.000 --> 11:34.000
To Prague.

11:36.000 --> 11:37.000
I understand now.

11:39.000 --> 11:42.000
The room was suddenly very quiet.

11:44.000 --> 11:47.000
Jan drank his cold coffee and waited.

11:48.000 --> 11:52.000
The old man took something out of his pocket.

11:53.000 --> 11:56.000
It was a photograph of his dead wife,

11:57.000 --> 11:58.000
Jan's mother.

12:00.000 --> 12:02.000
He spoke very quietly,

12:03.000 --> 12:04.000
not to Jan,

12:05.000 --> 12:08.000
but to the photograph in his hand.

12:10.000 --> 12:12.000
Perhaps now,

12:13.000 --> 12:14.000
before I die,

12:15.000 --> 12:16.000
just once,

12:17.000 --> 12:18.000
I can go back again.

12:21.000 --> 12:23.000
Carol came back with some hot coffee.

12:25.000 --> 12:26.000
She looked at Joseph,

12:27.000 --> 12:28.000
then at Jan.

12:30.000 --> 12:31.000
Shh.

12:32.000 --> 12:33.000
He's thinking about Prague.

12:34.000 --> 12:35.000
Jan said quietly.

12:38.000 --> 12:40.000
Carol put the coffee on the table

12:41.000 --> 12:42.000
and sat down.

12:44.000 --> 12:49.000
The hands on the clock slowly moved through two long minutes.

12:51.000 --> 12:55.000
Then the old man put the photograph back in his pocket.

12:57.000 --> 12:59.000
All right, he said.

13:00.000 --> 13:03.000
Let's all go to Prague for Christmas.

13:04.000 --> 13:06.000
It's beautiful there when it snows.

13:07.000 --> 13:09.000
I remember it so well.

13:10.000 --> 13:11.000
So very well.

13:14.000 --> 13:30.000
Chapter 3. The Accident.

13:33.000 --> 13:36.000
The first rehearsal began at nine o'clock

13:37.000 --> 13:39.000
and finished at two o'clock.

13:41.000 --> 13:43.000
What a long morning!

13:44.000 --> 13:45.000
Everyone said.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.000
I'm sorry,

13:49.000 --> 13:50.000
said the conductor,

13:51.000 --> 13:53.000
but we have very little time.

13:54.000 --> 13:56.000
The first concert is tomorrow night

13:57.000 --> 14:00.000
and a lot of important people are coming.

14:01.000 --> 14:03.000
So we must play well.

14:04.000 --> 14:07.000
Now, please go and eat.

14:08.000 --> 14:10.000
This afternoon is free.

14:11.000 --> 14:15.000
So you can go and look at this beautiful city.

14:16.000 --> 14:21.000
Tomorrow morning we begin again at nine o'clock.

14:21.000 --> 14:24.000
Please don't be late.

14:26.000 --> 14:29.000
Carol left the rehearsal room with Alan,

14:30.000 --> 14:32.000
one of the first violinists.

14:34.000 --> 14:37.000
What are you going to do this afternoon, Carol?

14:38.000 --> 14:39.000
Alan asked.

14:40.000 --> 14:42.000
I'm going to get a quick sandwich

14:43.000 --> 14:45.000
and then I'm going shopping.

14:46.000 --> 14:47.000
Carol said.

14:48.000 --> 14:53.000
My husband, Jan and his father are arriving on Sunday.

14:54.000 --> 14:56.000
Monday is Christmas day

14:57.000 --> 14:59.000
and I haven't got any presents for them.

15:00.000 --> 15:03.000
I must find something this afternoon.

15:04.000 --> 15:06.000
Our only free afternoon.

15:07.000 --> 15:09.000
See you tomorrow then.

15:10.000 --> 15:11.000
Said Alan.

15:12.000 --> 15:14.000
And good luck with the shopping.

15:15.000 --> 15:17.000
Thanks, Carol said.

15:19.000 --> 15:22.000
There are some wonderful shops in the Starry Mesto,

15:23.000 --> 15:24.000
the old town.

15:25.000 --> 15:27.000
So I'm going down there.

15:30.000 --> 15:33.000
Carol went into a lot of shops that afternoon.

15:36.000 --> 15:39.000
In the end, she got a book for Jan

15:40.000 --> 15:42.000
and a picture for his father.

15:44.000 --> 15:46.000
When she left the old town,

15:47.000 --> 15:49.000
it was nearly dark.

15:50.000 --> 15:52.000
It was very cold.

15:53.000 --> 15:55.000
So she walked quickly through the streets,

15:56.000 --> 15:58.000
back to her hotel.

15:59.000 --> 16:03.000
There were Christmas trees in all the shop windows

16:04.000 --> 16:06.000
and the city looked beautiful.

16:08.000 --> 16:10.000
There was a lot of noise too.

16:11.000 --> 16:16.000
People, cars, taxis, buses.

16:18.000 --> 16:20.000
Everybody's doing their Christmas shopping,

16:21.000 --> 16:22.000
Carol thought.

16:24.000 --> 16:28.000
Suddenly, she saw a man across the street.

16:29.000 --> 16:30.000
It was Jan.

16:31.000 --> 16:33.000
Why was he in Prague so soon?

16:35.000 --> 16:36.000
Jan?

16:37.000 --> 16:39.000
She shouted across the street.

16:40.000 --> 16:42.000
But Jan didn't hear her.

16:43.000 --> 16:44.000
He walked on.

16:46.000 --> 16:47.000
Carol shouted again.

16:48.000 --> 16:49.000
Very loudly.

16:50.000 --> 16:51.000
Jan?

16:52.000 --> 16:53.000
Jan?

16:53.000 --> 16:55.000
It's me, Carol.

16:56.000 --> 16:59.000
A lot of people stopped this time.

17:00.000 --> 17:02.000
They all looked at her.

17:04.000 --> 17:06.000
The man stopped too.

17:07.000 --> 17:10.000
He turned and looked at Carol for a minute.

17:12.000 --> 17:13.000
But he didn't smile.

17:14.000 --> 17:15.000
And he didn't speak.

17:17.000 --> 17:19.000
It was a very long minute for Carol.

17:21.000 --> 17:23.000
Her husband's eyes were cold.

17:24.000 --> 17:27.000
And Carol began to feel afraid.

17:28.000 --> 17:33.000
Then he moved and began to walk away from Carol

17:34.000 --> 17:36.000
down a little street.

17:38.000 --> 17:40.000
Carol did not understand it.

17:41.000 --> 17:43.000
But she knew one thing.

17:44.000 --> 17:46.000
She did not want to lose him.

17:48.000 --> 17:50.000
Perhaps he didn't see me very well.

17:51.000 --> 17:53.000
It's so dark now.

17:54.000 --> 17:55.000
He's going.

17:56.000 --> 17:57.000
Where is he going?

17:58.000 --> 17:59.000
Jan?

18:00.000 --> 18:01.000
Come back.

18:02.000 --> 18:03.000
Are you ill?

18:04.000 --> 18:06.000
She ran across the street.

18:07.000 --> 18:09.000
There was a sudden noise.

18:10.000 --> 18:11.000
And somebody shouted.

18:12.000 --> 18:14.000
Two seconds later,

18:14.000 --> 18:16.000
Carol lay in the snow.

18:17.000 --> 18:19.000
She ran right in front of me.

18:20.000 --> 18:22.000
The bus driver said later.

18:23.000 --> 18:24.000
I couldn't stop.

18:25.000 --> 18:26.000
There was no time.

18:28.000 --> 18:30.000
Carol's face was white.

18:31.000 --> 18:33.000
And her eyes were closed.

18:35.000 --> 18:40.000
Soon an ambulance came and took her body away.

18:41.000 --> 18:42.000
Was she alive?

18:42.000 --> 18:43.000
Or dead?

18:45.000 --> 18:47.000
At nine o'clock the next morning,

18:48.000 --> 18:51.000
the conductor was ready to begin the rehearsal.

18:52.000 --> 18:55.000
He opened his music and the orchestra started to play.

18:59.000 --> 19:02.000
Suddenly, his hands stopped moving

19:03.000 --> 19:05.000
and the music stopped at once.

19:12.000 --> 19:13.000
Harpist?

19:14.000 --> 19:16.000
The conductor shouted angrily.

19:17.000 --> 19:18.000
What's the matter with you?

19:19.000 --> 19:20.000
Are you sleeping?

19:21.000 --> 19:23.000
You begin to play here.

19:25.000 --> 19:27.000
Excuse me, Mr. Renaldi?

19:28.000 --> 19:30.000
Said someone at the back of the room.

19:31.000 --> 19:33.000
The harpist is not here.

19:35.000 --> 19:38.000
Everyone turned and looked at the harp

19:38.000 --> 19:40.000
at the back of the orchestra.

19:41.000 --> 19:42.000
It was true.

19:44.000 --> 19:46.000
There was nobody in the harpist's chair.

19:48.000 --> 19:50.000
Well, where is she?

19:51.000 --> 19:52.000
Ask the conductor.

19:54.000 --> 19:55.000
There was no answer.

19:57.000 --> 19:59.000
We can't wait for her, he said.

20:01.000 --> 20:03.000
We must have this rehearsal without her.

20:05.000 --> 20:06.000
Where is Alan?

20:07.000 --> 20:08.000
He can speak some check.

20:10.000 --> 20:11.000
Alan stood up.

20:13.000 --> 20:16.000
Can you go to the hotel and look for her there?

20:17.000 --> 20:18.000
The conductor asked.

20:20.000 --> 20:24.000
Then come back here at once, with or without her.

20:26.000 --> 20:27.000
Alan left.

20:29.000 --> 20:31.000
Half an hour later, he was back.

20:34.000 --> 20:36.000
She's not at the hotel, he said.

20:37.000 --> 20:40.000
I spoke to two or three people in the hotel.

20:41.000 --> 20:45.000
And they say that Carol wasn't there at breakfast this morning.

20:47.000 --> 20:51.000
And they think that she didn't sleep in her room last night.

20:53.000 --> 20:55.000
I don't like this.

20:56.000 --> 20:57.000
Said the conductor.

20:58.000 --> 21:00.000
Carol is never late for rehearsals.

21:01.000 --> 21:05.000
And she knows that these concerts are important for us.

21:07.000 --> 21:09.000
I think we must tell the police.

21:11.000 --> 21:12.000
Shall I do it now?

21:13.000 --> 21:14.000
Alan asked.

21:15.000 --> 21:17.000
Yes, said the conductor.

21:18.000 --> 21:19.000
Please go now.

21:19.000 --> 21:20.000
Please go now.

21:35.000 --> 21:36.000
Chapter 4

21:37.000 --> 21:39.000
Nobody understands Carol.

21:42.000 --> 21:45.000
Carol slowly opened her eyes.

21:46.000 --> 21:48.000
Her head hurt.

21:49.000 --> 21:51.000
She closed her eyes again.

21:52.000 --> 21:54.000
A man said something.

21:55.000 --> 21:56.000
What was it?

21:58.000 --> 21:59.000
Carol.

22:00.000 --> 22:01.000
She heard.

22:02.000 --> 22:03.000
Carol.

22:04.000 --> 22:05.000
Can you hear me?

22:07.000 --> 22:08.000
I can hear you.

22:09.000 --> 22:10.000
Carol said.

22:11.000 --> 22:14.000
But I don't want to open my eyes.

22:15.000 --> 22:17.000
My head hurts.

22:19.000 --> 22:20.000
Who are you?

22:22.000 --> 22:23.000
It's me.

22:24.000 --> 22:25.000
Your Georinaldi.

22:26.000 --> 22:28.000
The conductor of the orchestra.

22:31.000 --> 22:32.000
Mr. Analdi.

22:34.000 --> 22:36.000
Carol opened her eyes again.

22:37.000 --> 22:40.000
Her head didn't hurt so much this time.

22:42.000 --> 22:44.000
What are you doing in my bedroom?

22:45.000 --> 22:46.000
She asked angrily.

22:47.000 --> 22:48.000
What's happening?

22:50.000 --> 22:52.000
This isn't your bedroom.

22:53.000 --> 22:54.000
Said Mr. Analdi.

22:55.000 --> 22:58.000
It's a hospital in Prague.

22:59.000 --> 23:01.000
You had an accident yesterday.

23:02.000 --> 23:05.000
Can you remember anything about it?

23:07.000 --> 23:10.000
Suddenly Carol remembered everything.

23:11.000 --> 23:12.000
The old town.

23:13.000 --> 23:15.000
The Christmas trees in the shop windows.

23:16.000 --> 23:17.000
Christmas presents.

23:18.000 --> 23:19.000
Jan.

23:20.000 --> 23:21.000
Jan!

23:22.000 --> 23:23.000
She sat up.

23:24.000 --> 23:25.000
Jan!

23:26.000 --> 23:27.000
Where's Jan?

23:28.000 --> 23:29.000
She asked Mr. Analdi.

23:30.000 --> 23:32.000
Please, Mrs. Black.

23:33.000 --> 23:34.000
Said a woman quietly.

23:35.000 --> 23:36.000
Don't get excited.

23:37.000 --> 23:38.000
Lie down again.

23:40.000 --> 23:41.000
Carol turned her head.

23:43.000 --> 23:44.000
It hurt again.

23:45.000 --> 23:47.000
Near the door of the room.

23:48.000 --> 23:50.000
She saw a woman in a white coat.

23:51.000 --> 23:52.000
A doctor.

23:54.000 --> 23:56.000
But I must see Jan.

23:57.000 --> 23:58.000
Carol said.

23:59.000 --> 24:00.000
Where is he?

24:01.000 --> 24:02.000
I must find him.

24:03.000 --> 24:04.000
I can't.

24:05.000 --> 24:06.000
Oh dear.

24:07.000 --> 24:08.000
She put her hand to her head.

24:09.000 --> 24:10.000
Who's Jan?

24:11.000 --> 24:13.000
The doctor asked Mr. Analdi quietly.

24:15.000 --> 24:16.000
Her husband.

24:17.000 --> 24:18.000
He answered.

24:19.000 --> 24:21.000
He took Carol's hand.

24:22.000 --> 24:23.000
Listen.

24:24.000 --> 24:26.000
Your husband is coming.

24:27.000 --> 24:29.000
We told him about the accident.

24:30.000 --> 24:33.000
He's on a plane from London now.

24:35.000 --> 24:36.000
On a plane?

24:37.000 --> 24:38.000
Why?

24:39.000 --> 24:40.000
He's here in Prague.

24:41.000 --> 24:43.000
I saw him in the street.

24:44.000 --> 24:45.000
The old town.

24:46.000 --> 24:47.000
I called out to him.

24:48.000 --> 24:49.000
And he saw me.

24:50.000 --> 24:51.000
But he didn't stop.

24:53.000 --> 24:55.000
He just walked away from me.

24:57.000 --> 24:58.000
Please find him.

24:59.000 --> 25:00.000
Please.

25:00.000 --> 25:01.000
I must talk to him.

25:02.000 --> 25:03.000
I must.

25:05.000 --> 25:07.000
The doctor moved nearer to the bed.

25:09.000 --> 25:11.000
Jan is coming soon, Mrs. Black.

25:11.000 --> 25:12.000
Mrs. Black.

25:12.000 --> 25:13.000
She said.

25:14.000 --> 25:16.000
Please don't get excited.

25:16.000 --> 25:18.000
It's not good for you.

25:19.000 --> 25:20.000
Now,

25:20.000 --> 25:21.000
lie down again

25:22.000 --> 25:24.000
and close your eyes.

25:25.000 --> 25:26.000
You must sleep.

25:27.000 --> 25:30.000
And I know you're feeling very tired.

25:32.000 --> 25:35.000
Carol lay down and closed her eyes.

25:37.000 --> 25:38.000
The doctor was right.

25:39.000 --> 25:41.000
She was tired.

25:42.000 --> 25:44.000
But why didn't they listen?

25:45.000 --> 25:47.000
Why didn't they understand?

25:48.000 --> 25:52.000
Jan was in Prague and she must find him.

25:53.000 --> 25:54.000
Talk to him.

25:56.000 --> 26:01.000
The doctor looked at Mr. Inaldi and spoke very quietly.

26:02.000 --> 26:05.000
Let's leave her now, please.

26:06.000 --> 26:08.000
She needs to sleep.

26:09.000 --> 26:11.000
You can come back later.

26:13.000 --> 26:17.000
Mr. Inaldi and the doctor left the room.

26:18.000 --> 26:20.000
They closed the door quietly

26:21.000 --> 26:25.000
and then looked at Carol through the window in the door.

26:27.000 --> 26:29.000
She's going to be all right.

26:30.000 --> 26:31.000
Said the doctor.

26:32.000 --> 26:34.000
She just needs to sleep for a time.

26:35.000 --> 26:37.000
There's nothing wrong with her.

26:38.000 --> 26:40.000
Yes, there is.

26:41.000 --> 26:42.000
Said Mr. Inaldi.

26:43.000 --> 26:45.000
She thinks her husband is in Prague.

26:46.000 --> 26:50.000
But I spoke to him on the telephone three hours ago

26:51.000 --> 26:53.000
and he was in Oxford.

26:54.000 --> 26:56.000
I'm afraid she's ill.

26:57.000 --> 26:58.000
Very ill.

26:59.000 --> 27:00.000
Listen.

27:01.000 --> 27:02.000
Said the doctor.

27:02.000 --> 27:06.000
She had a bad hit on the head in the accident.

27:07.000 --> 27:09.000
But she didn't break anything.

27:10.000 --> 27:12.000
And her head is all right.

27:14.000 --> 27:16.000
We looked at it very carefully.

27:17.000 --> 27:22.000
She's going to be okay after a good sleep.

27:23.000 --> 27:28.000
But all this talk about Jan her husband.

27:29.000 --> 27:30.000
Said Mr. Inaldi.

27:31.000 --> 27:32.000
What about that?

27:34.000 --> 27:37.000
Yes. She's confused about that.

27:38.000 --> 27:39.000
It's true.

27:40.000 --> 27:42.000
But she remembers her name.

27:43.000 --> 27:44.000
She knows you.

27:46.000 --> 27:49.000
And she understands that she's in hospital.

27:50.000 --> 27:52.000
All this is very good.

27:54.000 --> 27:57.000
Now, what about you, Mr. Inaldi?

27:58.000 --> 28:01.000
It's a difficult time for you too.

28:02.000 --> 28:04.000
Because of your concerts.

28:05.000 --> 28:06.000
I understand that.

28:07.000 --> 28:09.000
But please go away now.

28:10.000 --> 28:11.000
Eat something.

28:12.000 --> 28:13.000
Have a sleep.

28:14.000 --> 28:16.000
Then come back later this afternoon.

28:17.000 --> 28:19.000
You can't do anything now.

28:21.000 --> 28:22.000
All right.

28:23.000 --> 28:24.000
Said Mr. Inaldi.

28:25.000 --> 28:27.000
But he was not happy.

28:28.000 --> 28:29.000
Poor Carol.

28:30.000 --> 28:31.000
He thought.

28:32.000 --> 28:34.000
And my poor orchestra.

28:35.000 --> 28:40.000
How can I find another harpist before tonight's concert?

28:55.000 --> 28:56.000
Chapter 5.

28:57.000 --> 28:59.000
Some visitors for Carol.

29:02.000 --> 29:07.000
Two hours later, a tall man arrived at the hospital.

29:09.000 --> 29:13.000
He asked to see the woman in yesterday's street accident.

29:15.000 --> 29:16.000
He didn't know her name.

29:18.000 --> 29:20.000
The doctor came downstairs.

29:21.000 --> 29:23.000
Who are you?

29:24.000 --> 29:26.000
She asked the man.

29:27.000 --> 29:30.000
My name is Parvell Brechter.

29:31.000 --> 29:33.000
I saw the accident.

29:34.000 --> 29:36.000
And I called the ambulance.

29:37.000 --> 29:39.000
Is the woman all right?

29:40.000 --> 29:42.000
I just wanted to know that.

29:43.000 --> 29:45.000
I was afraid she was dead.

29:46.000 --> 29:48.000
The doctor smiled.

29:49.000 --> 29:51.000
Would you like to see her?

29:52.000 --> 29:54.000
She's much better now.

29:55.000 --> 29:56.000
Yes, please.

29:57.000 --> 29:59.000
Answer, Parvell.

30:00.000 --> 30:02.000
Then come with me.

30:03.000 --> 30:06.000
They went upstairs in the lift

30:07.000 --> 30:09.000
and walked along to Carol's room.

30:11.000 --> 30:13.000
At the door they stopped.

30:13.000 --> 30:16.000
And looked in through the window.

30:17.000 --> 30:19.000
She's sleeping.

30:20.000 --> 30:22.000
Said the doctor.

30:23.000 --> 30:25.000
But she looks well.

30:26.000 --> 30:27.000
Said Parvell.

30:28.000 --> 30:31.000
Yesterday she looked so white.

30:32.000 --> 30:34.000
I was afraid for her.

30:36.000 --> 30:40.000
Just then Carol opened her eyes

30:41.000 --> 30:45.000
and saw a man through the window in her door.

30:46.000 --> 30:47.000
She sat up.

30:49.000 --> 30:50.000
Jan!

30:50.000 --> 30:51.000
She shouted.

30:52.000 --> 30:53.000
Jan!

30:54.000 --> 30:55.000
Oh dear.

30:56.000 --> 30:59.000
The doctor said, not again.

31:01.000 --> 31:03.000
She hit her head in the accident

31:04.000 --> 31:07.000
and she's confused about some things.

31:08.000 --> 31:12.000
She thinks that you are her husband from England.

31:14.000 --> 31:15.000
Shall I go?

31:16.000 --> 31:17.000
Asked Parvell.

31:18.000 --> 31:19.000
Perhaps it's better.

31:20.000 --> 31:21.000
Yes.

31:22.000 --> 31:23.000
Answer the doctor.

31:25.000 --> 31:28.000
She went into Carol's room and closed the door.

31:30.000 --> 31:32.000
Parvell walked slowly back to the lift.

31:33.000 --> 31:38.000
Then the lift door opened and a man ran out

31:39.000 --> 31:42.000
with some beautiful red flowers in his arms.

31:43.000 --> 31:46.000
He looked at the numbers of the rooms

31:47.000 --> 31:50.000
and then went quickly into Carol's room.

31:51.000 --> 31:53.000
He didn't see Parvell.

31:54.000 --> 31:58.000
But an older man came slowly out of the lift next.

31:59.000 --> 32:03.000
He saw Parvell and stopped suddenly.

32:04.000 --> 32:06.000
Parvell stopped too.

32:08.000 --> 32:11.000
I'm sorry, said the old man.

32:12.000 --> 32:15.000
My eyes aren't very good.

32:16.000 --> 32:20.000
I thought, you see, you look.

32:21.000 --> 32:25.000
Yes, I know, said Parvell.

32:25.000 --> 32:26.000
Said Parvell.

32:27.000 --> 32:28.000
I saw your friend.

32:30.000 --> 32:31.000
He's not my friend.

32:33.000 --> 32:34.000
He's my son.

32:35.000 --> 32:37.000
Please tell me.

32:38.000 --> 32:39.000
What is your name?

32:41.000 --> 32:42.000
Parvell Brickter.

32:44.000 --> 32:46.000
The old man looked very afraid.

32:48.000 --> 32:52.000
His face went white and his mouth opened and closed.

32:53.000 --> 32:55.000
But he said nothing.

32:56.000 --> 32:58.000
Now Parvell was afraid.

33:00.000 --> 33:03.000
You don't look very well, he said.

33:04.000 --> 33:08.000
Would you like to sit down and shall I call a doctor?

33:09.000 --> 33:11.000
There's a doctor in this room here.

33:13.000 --> 33:15.000
Please, said the old man.

33:16.000 --> 33:19.000
My son is in that room.

33:20.000 --> 33:22.000
Please take me to him.

33:23.000 --> 33:26.000
Parvell took the old man's arm.

33:29.000 --> 33:36.000
In Carol's room, Jan put the red flowers on the bed and took his wife's hands.

33:38.000 --> 33:42.000
Oh, my love. Are you all right? He said.

33:43.000 --> 33:45.000
I can't understand it.

33:46.000 --> 33:50.000
Why did you run in front of a bus? How did it happen?

33:52.000 --> 33:55.000
Carol didn't answer his questions.

33:57.000 --> 34:00.000
Jan, she looked up into his face.

34:02.000 --> 34:05.000
You are Jan. Tell me that you're Jan.

34:07.000 --> 34:11.000
Of course I'm Jan. What are you talking about?

34:12.000 --> 34:15.000
The doctor came up to the bed.

34:16.000 --> 34:19.000
Wait a minute, she said.

34:20.000 --> 34:24.000
You told me that your name was Parvell Britta.

34:25.000 --> 34:29.000
Are you Mrs. Black's husband or not?

34:31.000 --> 34:35.000
Just then, Carol looked behind Jan.

34:36.000 --> 34:42.000
She saw Parvell with Jan's father through the window of her door.

34:43.000 --> 34:46.000
Her eyes got bigger and bigger.

34:47.000 --> 34:54.000
Who is that? She said.

34:55.000 --> 34:59.000
Jan and the doctor turned and saw Parvell.

35:00.000 --> 35:04.000
My God, said Jan.

35:05.000 --> 35:07.000
I don't know.

35:08.000 --> 35:11.000
The doctor looked back at Jan's face.

35:12.000 --> 35:19.000
Two men, but only one face, she said quietly.

35:21.000 --> 35:27.000
Then Jan's father opened the door of Carol's room and the two men came in.

35:28.000 --> 35:30.000
Jan stood up.

35:31.000 --> 35:33.000
He looked at his father.

35:34.000 --> 35:36.000
Who is this man?

35:37.000 --> 35:39.000
He asked.

35:40.000 --> 35:43.000
His name is Parvell Britta.

35:44.000 --> 35:46.000
He answered his father.

35:47.000 --> 35:51.000
Please, bring me a chair and some water.

35:51.000 --> 35:56.000
I need to sit down before I can answer your question.

35:58.000 --> 36:03.000
Jan got a chair for his father and the doctor gave him some water.

36:04.000 --> 36:09.000
Then she left the room quietly.

36:22.000 --> 36:28.000
Chapter 6. Who is Parvell?

36:29.000 --> 36:34.000
The old man drank some water and looked up.

36:35.000 --> 36:37.000
Parvell, he said.

36:38.000 --> 36:42.000
I must ask you to look at this photo.

36:43.000 --> 36:48.000
He put his hand in his pocket and took out a photograph.

36:48.000 --> 36:53.000
And took out a photograph of a young woman.

36:54.000 --> 36:57.000
Do you know this woman?

36:59.000 --> 37:01.000
Yes, said Parvell.

37:02.000 --> 37:06.000
That's a photo of my mother, Lenka.

37:07.000 --> 37:10.000
She died when I was very young.

37:11.000 --> 37:17.000
But my grandmother had many photos of her and we often looked at them.

37:19.000 --> 37:24.000
Did you live with your grandmother when you were young?

37:25.000 --> 37:27.000
Yes, I did.

37:28.000 --> 37:31.000
But how do you know all this?

37:32.000 --> 37:39.000
Because, said Joseph, Lenka was my wife.

37:41.000 --> 37:44.000
Dad, what are you saying?

37:44.000 --> 37:46.000
Said Jan.

37:47.000 --> 37:49.000
Joseph looked at Jan.

37:50.000 --> 37:51.000
My boy.

37:52.000 --> 37:54.000
Don't be angry with me.

37:56.000 --> 38:00.000
I didn't tell you many things about your mother.

38:01.000 --> 38:03.000
Perhaps I was wrong.

38:05.000 --> 38:07.000
But I wanted to forget.

38:08.000 --> 38:10.000
Not to forget your mother.

38:11.000 --> 38:16.000
Only to forget that terrible night in 1957.

38:18.000 --> 38:24.000
Jan, this man, Parvell, is your twin brother.

38:26.000 --> 38:28.000
You can see that it's true.

38:29.000 --> 38:31.000
Look at your faces.

38:33.000 --> 38:35.000
Parvell looked at Jan.

38:36.000 --> 38:41.000
So, I have a brother, he said.

38:42.000 --> 38:45.000
My grandmother never told me that.

38:46.000 --> 38:48.000
Jan smiled.

38:49.000 --> 38:58.000
And my father, our father, never told me about a twin brother.

38:59.000 --> 39:01.000
He turned to Joseph.

39:02.000 --> 39:05.000
Dad, why didn't you tell me?

39:07.000 --> 39:09.000
It's a long story.

39:10.000 --> 39:12.000
Said the old man.

39:13.000 --> 39:20.000
It begins many years ago, when a young man went to Prague University.

39:21.000 --> 39:24.000
He was there for seven years.

39:25.000 --> 39:30.000
And in his last year, he met a beautiful young woman.

39:32.000 --> 39:34.000
His eyes turned to the photo.

39:36.000 --> 39:38.000
She was so beautiful.

39:40.000 --> 39:44.000
Of course, the young man fell in love with her.

39:45.000 --> 39:48.000
And they got married in 1956.

39:50.000 --> 39:53.000
But things were difficult in Prague then.

39:54.000 --> 39:55.000
People were not happy.

39:56.000 --> 39:58.000
And they were not free.

39:59.000 --> 40:06.000
Lenka and I, and a lot of our friends, wanted to change things.

40:07.000 --> 40:09.000
But it was dangerous work.

40:10.000 --> 40:15.000
The Russians knew about us, and they watched us all the time.

40:17.000 --> 40:25.000
Then you two boys were born on a wonderful day in June 1957.

40:26.000 --> 40:28.000
But you went away.

40:29.000 --> 40:30.000
Parvel said angrily.

40:31.000 --> 40:34.000
Your wife died, and you left the country.

40:35.000 --> 40:39.000
You went away to England, and began a new life.

40:41.000 --> 40:42.000
You didn't write.

40:43.000 --> 40:44.000
You didn't telephone.

40:45.000 --> 40:47.000
You weren't interested in me.

40:48.000 --> 40:49.000
Your son.

40:50.000 --> 40:53.000
Yoursif's face was very sad.

40:54.000 --> 41:00.000
Parvel, he said, I thought you were dead.

41:02.000 --> 41:05.000
Look, I must show you something.

41:07.000 --> 41:14.000
From behind the photo of his wife, he took out a letter and gave it to Parvel.

41:15.000 --> 41:18.000
The letter was old and yellow.

41:19.000 --> 41:24.000
Parvel opened it and began to read.

41:25.000 --> 41:31.000
The letter was in check, and it was his grandmother's writing.

41:33.000 --> 41:39.000
I write to tell you, Yoursif, that your wife is dead.

41:40.000 --> 41:47.000
On Christmas night, the guards shot her on the road at the border.

41:48.000 --> 41:58.000
She carried Parvel, your baby's son, and my grandson, on her back.

41:59.000 --> 42:01.000
And the guards shot him too.

42:02.000 --> 42:06.000
Your wife and your son are dead.

42:07.000 --> 42:12.000
Your friends came and told me yesterday.

42:13.000 --> 42:18.000
You have yarn, and a new life in England.

42:19.000 --> 42:21.000
And what do I have?

42:22.000 --> 42:23.000
Nothing.

42:24.000 --> 42:27.000
You took one grandson away from me.

42:28.000 --> 42:33.000
And now my daughter and little Parvel are dead.

42:34.000 --> 42:36.000
Because of you.

42:37.000 --> 42:39.000
Don't write to me.

42:40.000 --> 42:42.000
And don't come back to Prague.

42:43.000 --> 42:49.000
I never want to see you or hear from you again.

42:50.000 --> 42:51.000
Stanner's lover.

42:54.000 --> 42:57.000
Slowly Parvel put the letter down.

42:58.000 --> 43:00.000
I understand now.

43:01.000 --> 43:03.000
He said quietly.

43:04.000 --> 43:06.000
What a terrible letter.

43:07.000 --> 43:09.000
How could she do that to you?

43:10.000 --> 43:12.000
And to me.

43:13.000 --> 43:17.000
Stanner's lover loved her daughter very much.

43:18.000 --> 43:20.000
Yoursif said sadly.

43:21.000 --> 43:23.000
She loved you too.

43:24.000 --> 43:26.000
And didn't want to lose you.

43:27.000 --> 43:29.000
I see that now.

43:30.000 --> 43:32.000
But she never liked me.

43:33.000 --> 43:38.000
And after that letter, how could I go back to Prague?

43:39.000 --> 43:41.000
You were dead.

43:42.000 --> 43:44.000
Lenko was dead.

43:45.000 --> 43:47.000
He put his face in his hands.

43:49.000 --> 43:51.000
The room was very quiet.

43:52.000 --> 43:56.000
Then Parvel put his hand on his father's arm.

43:58.000 --> 44:01.000
Stanner's lover is dead now.

44:02.000 --> 44:03.000
He said.

44:04.000 --> 44:06.000
You and I can begin again.

44:07.000 --> 44:08.000
He smiled.

44:09.000 --> 44:12.000
And learned to be father and son.

44:15.000 --> 44:18.000
Yoursif's face was wet with tears.

44:19.000 --> 44:22.000
He put his hand over Parvel's hand.

44:23.000 --> 44:25.000
And smiled back at him.

44:26.000 --> 44:28.000
But he could not speak.

44:29.000 --> 44:32.000
Now there were tears in everybody's eyes.

44:35.000 --> 44:38.000
After a minute or two, Jan said.

44:39.000 --> 44:43.000
Dad, I know it's difficult for you.

44:43.000 --> 44:48.000
But can you tell us about that Christmas in 1957?

44:50.000 --> 44:52.000
How did it all happen?

44:53.000 --> 44:55.000
I'd like to know.

44:56.000 --> 44:57.000
Yes.

44:58.000 --> 44:59.000
Said his father.

45:00.000 --> 45:03.000
You and Parvel must know.

45:05.000 --> 45:06.000
He turned to Parvel.

45:08.000 --> 45:11.000
But what did Stanner's lover tell you?

45:14.000 --> 45:16.000
Very little, Parvel said.

45:17.000 --> 45:20.000
She never wanted to talk about it.

45:21.000 --> 45:24.000
She told me that my mother died in hospital.

45:25.000 --> 45:27.000
And you went away to England.

45:28.000 --> 45:29.000
That was all.

45:30.000 --> 45:32.000
I can understand that.

45:33.000 --> 45:34.000
Said hissif.

45:35.000 --> 45:37.000
Poor Stanner's lover.

45:38.000 --> 45:41.000
She lost her daughter because of me.

45:42.000 --> 45:46.000
And she never liked our work for freedom, you see.

45:47.000 --> 45:49.000
She didn't understand.

45:50.000 --> 45:53.000
She just wanted a quiet family life.

45:55.000 --> 45:57.000
Christmas 1957.

45:58.000 --> 45:59.000
Said Jan.

46:00.000 --> 46:01.000
Yes.

46:02.000 --> 46:03.000
Said hissif.

46:04.000 --> 46:07.000
In October and November of that year,

46:08.000 --> 46:12.000
things got more and more dangerous for Lenka and me.

46:13.000 --> 46:18.000
Our friends told us, leave before the Russians get you.

46:19.000 --> 46:23.000
Get away to Austria and then to England.

46:25.000 --> 46:29.000
We didn't want to leave Czechoslovakia, of course.

46:30.000 --> 46:31.000
It was our home.

46:32.000 --> 46:34.000
But we couldn't stay.

46:35.000 --> 46:37.000
Our friends helped us.

46:37.000 --> 46:42.000
And Jan and I got across the border on the day before Christmas,

46:43.000 --> 46:45.000
December the 24th.

46:46.000 --> 46:47.000
It was night.

46:48.000 --> 46:49.000
There was no moon.

46:50.000 --> 46:54.000
And we got to Austria all right through the fields and the snow.

46:56.000 --> 46:58.000
But the next night.

46:59.000 --> 47:02.000
December the 25th, said Parvel.

47:03.000 --> 47:05.000
My grandmother told me the day.

47:06.000 --> 47:10.000
My mother died in a hospital bed in Prague, she said.

47:12.000 --> 47:15.000
Lenka died in the snow.

47:16.000 --> 47:18.000
On the road at the border.

47:19.000 --> 47:20.000
Yes, if said.

47:21.000 --> 47:24.000
She was so near Austria.

47:25.000 --> 47:27.000
So near us.

47:28.000 --> 47:30.000
With you, Parvel.

47:31.000 --> 47:32.000
On her back.

47:34.000 --> 47:36.000
The old man's voice stopped.

47:37.000 --> 47:41.000
And again, he put his head in his hands.

47:41.000 --> 47:43.000
Chapter 7.

47:57.000 --> 48:00.000
The music must come first.

48:03.000 --> 48:07.000
For some minutes, nobody in the rooms said anything.

48:08.000 --> 48:11.000
They looked at the old man in his chair.

48:12.000 --> 48:17.000
And they all thought about a snowy night in 1957.

48:18.000 --> 48:21.000
Then Parvel turned to Jan.

48:23.000 --> 48:28.000
Let's forget 1957 for now, he said quietly.

48:29.000 --> 48:33.000
For me, this is a wonderful day.

48:34.000 --> 48:36.000
I have no family in Prague.

48:37.000 --> 48:40.000
My grandmother died many years ago.

48:41.000 --> 48:46.000
But now I have a brother, a father.

48:48.000 --> 48:51.000
He looked at Carol in her bed and smiled.

48:52.000 --> 48:54.000
And her sister.

48:56.000 --> 48:59.000
Why did you come to the hospital to see me?

49:00.000 --> 49:01.000
Carol asked.

49:03.000 --> 49:06.000
You had an accident because of me.

49:07.000 --> 49:08.000
Parvel said.

49:09.000 --> 49:10.000
I knew that.

49:11.000 --> 49:14.000
You called to me and shouted.

49:15.000 --> 49:18.000
And then ran to me across the street.

49:19.000 --> 49:21.000
Right in front of a bus.

49:22.000 --> 49:24.000
I didn't understand why.

49:25.000 --> 49:28.000
But I wanted to know that you were all right.

49:29.000 --> 49:31.000
Jan looked at Carol too.

49:33.000 --> 49:35.000
And are you all right, my love?

49:36.000 --> 49:37.000
I'm sorry.

49:38.000 --> 49:39.000
I forgot about you.

49:41.000 --> 49:43.000
I'm feeling very well.

49:44.000 --> 49:45.000
Carol said happily.

49:46.000 --> 49:49.000
Now I understand everything.

49:50.000 --> 49:52.000
So I feel much better.

49:53.000 --> 49:56.000
My husband is my husband again.

49:57.000 --> 49:59.000
And we have a new brother.

50:00.000 --> 50:01.000
Oh.

50:02.000 --> 50:03.000
But there is one thing.

50:05.000 --> 50:07.000
She looked at her new brother.

50:08.000 --> 50:14.000
Why is your name Parvel Britter and not Parvel Valak?

50:16.000 --> 50:18.000
The old man moved in his chair.

50:20.000 --> 50:23.000
Her name was Linka Britter.

50:24.000 --> 50:28.000
He said quietly before she married me.

50:29.000 --> 50:32.000
Yes, Parvel said.

50:33.000 --> 50:34.000
He looked at Carol.

50:36.000 --> 50:39.000
You see, my father didn't want me.

50:40.000 --> 50:41.000
I thought.

50:42.000 --> 50:44.000
So I didn't want my father's name.

50:45.000 --> 50:50.000
And when I was older, I changed it and took my mother's name.

50:51.000 --> 50:53.000
He turned to his father.

50:54.000 --> 50:57.000
I was an angry young man then.

50:58.000 --> 51:00.000
But now, no.

51:01.000 --> 51:02.000
Said Josef.

51:03.000 --> 51:04.000
Don't change it.

51:05.000 --> 51:06.000
It's a very good name.

51:07.000 --> 51:09.000
And you are Linka's son.

51:12.000 --> 51:17.000
Suddenly the door opened and Mr. Rinaldi came in.

51:18.000 --> 51:20.000
Carol, he said.

51:21.000 --> 51:23.000
The doctor says that you are better.

51:25.000 --> 51:26.000
Is it true?

51:27.000 --> 51:28.000
You look wonderful.

51:30.000 --> 51:32.000
Can you play in the concert tonight?

51:33.000 --> 51:36.000
You see, I can't find another harpist.

51:37.000 --> 51:40.000
And without a harp, the music.

51:41.000 --> 51:45.000
He saw everyone for the first time and stopped.

51:48.000 --> 51:49.000
I'm sorry.

51:50.000 --> 51:51.000
He said quickly.

51:52.000 --> 51:54.000
I see you have friends here.

51:55.000 --> 51:57.000
But you see, it's important.

51:58.000 --> 52:02.000
It's an important concert for my orchestra.

52:03.000 --> 52:05.000
And he stopped again.

52:06.000 --> 52:09.000
Why are you all laughing at me?

52:11.000 --> 52:13.000
Young stopped laughing first.

52:14.000 --> 52:16.000
Mr. Rinaldi, he said.

52:17.000 --> 52:22.000
You are the right man for Prague, the city of music.

52:23.000 --> 52:26.000
The music must come first.

52:28.000 --> 52:29.000
Carol?

52:30.000 --> 52:31.000
Mr. Rinaldi began.

52:32.000 --> 52:34.000
Carol turned to Jan.

52:36.000 --> 52:38.000
I feel very well now.

52:39.000 --> 52:41.000
And I'd like to play tonight.

52:42.000 --> 52:45.000
But I want all my family to come to the concert.

52:47.000 --> 52:53.000
My husband, my new brother, and their father.

52:54.000 --> 52:55.000
Can you all come?

52:56.000 --> 52:57.000
Please say yes.

52:59.000 --> 53:01.000
Jan looked at his father.

53:03.000 --> 53:05.000
Are you all right, Dad?

53:06.000 --> 53:08.000
Or are you feeling tired now?

53:09.000 --> 53:12.000
Shall we all go to Mr. Rinaldi's concert?

53:13.000 --> 53:17.000
Three tickets, of course, for all Carol's family.

53:18.000 --> 53:20.000
Said Mr. Rinaldi quickly.

53:22.000 --> 53:27.000
Christmas music in Prague again, Joseph said slowly.

53:28.000 --> 53:31.000
And with my two sons.

53:32.000 --> 53:36.000
Wonderful, wonderful.

53:37.000 --> 53:41.000
He smiled happily at Jan and Pavel.

53:42.000 --> 53:45.000
How can we say no?

53:46.000 --> 53:47.000
He asked.

54:06.000 --> 54:07.000
Thank you.

